[0.000, "o", "\u001b[3;3HIf you wish httpd to run as a different user or group, you must run\u001b[K\u001b[4;3Hhttpd as root initially and it will switch.\u001b[K\u001b[5;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[6dUser/Group: The name (or #number) of the user/group to run httpd as.\u001b[7;3HIt is usually good practice to create a dedicated user and group for\u001b[8;3Hrunning httpd, as with most system services.\u001b[K\r\u001b[10d"]
[0.000, "o", "User http\u001b[K\r\u001b[11dGroup http\u001b[K\r\u001b[12d\u001b[K\u001b[13d</IfModule>\r\u001b[14d"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[15d# 'Main'\u001b[16G configuration\u001b[K\u001b[16;3H\u001b[K\u001b[17dThe directives in this section set up the values used by the 'main'\u001b[K\u001b[18;3Hserver, which responds to any requests that aren't handled by a\u001b[K\u001b[19;3H<VirtualHost> definition.  These values also provide defaults for\u001b[K\u001b[20;3Hany <VirtualHost> containers you may define later in the file.\r\u001b[21d#\u001b[22d All of these directives may appear inside <VirtualHost> containers,\u001b[23;3Hin which case these default settings will be overridden for the"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[24;3H\u001b[30m\u001b[43mvirtual host\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000f being defined.\u001b[K\r\u001b[26d\u001b[K\u001b[27d# \u001b[K\u001b[28dServerAdmin: Your address, where problems with the server should be\u001b[K\u001b[29;3He-mailed.  This address appears on some server-generated pages, such\u001b[K\u001b[30;3Has error documents.  e.g. admin@your-domain.com\u001b[32;7HAdmin you@example.com\u001b[35;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "ServerName gives the name and port that the server uses to identify itself.\u001b[36;3HThis can often be determined automatically, but we recommend you specify\u001b[37;3Hit explicitly to prevent problems during startup.\u001b[38;3H\u001b[K\u001b[39dIf your host doesn't have a registered DNS name, enter its IP address here.\u001b[40;3H\u001b[K\u001b[41d\bServerName www.example.com:80\r\u001b[42d\u001b[K\u001b[43d#\u001b[44d "]
[0.000, "o", "Deny access to the entirety of your server's filesystem. You must\u001b[45;3Hexplicitly permit access to web content directories in other\u001b[K\u001b[24;3H"]
