[0.000, "o", "    Require all granted\r\u001b[3d</Directory>\u001b[K\r\u001b[4d\u001b[K\u001b[6d# "]
[0.000, "o", "DirectoryIndex: sets the file that Apache will serve if a directory\u001b[K\u001b[7;3His requested.\u001b[K\u001b[8;3H\u001b[K\r\u001b[9d<IfModule dir_module>\u001b[10;5HDirectoryIndex index.html\r\u001b[13d#\u001b[14d\b# The following lines prevent .htaccess and .htpasswd files from being\u001b[15;3Hviewed by Web clients.\u001b[K\r\u001b[17d<Files \".ht*\">\u001b[K\r\u001b[18d    Require all denied\u001b[K\r\u001b[19d</Files>\u001b[K\r\u001b[20d\u001b[K\u001b[22d# ErrorLog: The location of the error log file.\u001b[K\u001b[23;3HIf you do not specify an ErrorLog directive within a <VirtualHost>\u001b[24;3Hcontainer, error messages relating to that \u001b[30m\u001b[43mvirtual host\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000f will be\u001b[25;3Hlogged here.  If you *do* define an error logfile for a <VirtualHost>\r\u001b[26d# container, that host's errors will be logged there and not here.\r\u001b[28dErrorLog \"/var/log/httpd/error_log\"\u001b[K\r\u001b[29d\u001b[K\u001b[30d# \u001b[K\u001b[31dLogLevel: Control the number of messages logged to the error_log.\r\u001b[32d# Possible values include: debug, info, notice, warn, error, crit,\r\u001b[33d# alert, emerg.\r\u001b[35dLogLevel warn\u001b[K\r\u001b[36d\u001b[K\u001b[37d<IfModule log_config_module>\u001b[K\r\u001b[38d    #\r\u001b[39d    # The following directives define some format nicknames for use with\u001b[K\r\u001b[40d    # a CustomLog directive (see below).\r\u001b[41d    #\u001b[K\u001b[42d\bLogFormat \"%h %l %u %t \\\"%r\\\" %>s %b \\\"%{Referer}i\\\" \\\"%{User-Agent}i\\\"\" combined\r\u001b[43d    LogFormat \"%h %l %u %t \\\"%r\\\" %>s %b\" common\r\u001b[44d\u001b[K\u001b[45d    <IfModule logio_module>\u001b[K\u001b[24;46H"]
